          explanation: 'The moment M = r × F is a physical quantity — it does not depend on the coordinate system. While the individual components of M may change when you switch coordinate systems, the magnitude and direction of the moment vector remain the same. This is a fundamental property of vector cross products and is essential for ensuring that physical results are frame-independent.',
