          explanation: 'Replacing a distributed load requires two things: (1) the resultant force magnitude equals the area under the load distribution curve (e.g., w*L for uniform, w*L/2 for triangular), and (2) the resultant acts at the centroid of the load distribution (midpoint for uniform, 1/3 from the heavy end for triangular). Getting the magnitude right but the location wrong will produce incorrect moments and wrong support reactions. This is one of the most common errors in beam analysis.',
