          explanation: 'A frictionless pulley only changes the direction of the rope, not the tension magnitude. On the pulley FBD, the rope exerts two tension forces — one on each side — both equal to T and directed along the rope tangent on each side. The pulley axle also has a pin reaction. This is why pulleys are useful: they redirect force without diminishing it (in the ideal frictionless case). In reality, bearing friction causes a small difference between the two tensions.',
